text:
(1) A general view north from the Smith Street elevated station of the Eighth Avenue subway line, showing at the left, (steepled) the St. Mary's Roman Catholic facing Court Street, between Nelson and Luqueer Streets. From left to right in the background are the spires of Manhattan and midtown Brooklyn. This is located at 9th St.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, another view.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, showing the Williamsburg Bank Building of Brooklyn in the background.

P. L. Sperr.
title: General view - Brooklyn - 9th Street - Smith Street station - [8th Avenue Line.]

text:
A general view north from the Smith Street station of the Eighth Avenue subway line, located at 9th Street, showing in the background from left to right the spires of Manhattan and Brooklyn.

October 8, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
